Configure Management Syllabus 

Project 1

1. Set the background of the prompt of the master to red, for all users
2. Set the background of the prompt of the minion to green, for all users
3. Set the path for all users. the path can be arbitrary.
4. Set the MOTD for all users

Project 2
Configure / Setup NTP

1. Configure Master with NTP service
2. Configure Minion with NTP client
3. Change time manually on Master and see if time changes on the Minion and vice versa
4. Have NTP Autostart on boot
5. Check listening ports of the NTP service
 
Project 3
1. Configure/Setup Apache
2. Install/Start Apache
3. Configure Apache to serve web content from all home directories
4. Create "Hello World" page for 2 users
5. Startup Apache at boot
6. Configure Apache to run on port 8080
7. Run Apache not as root, but as a different user.

Project 4
1. Configure / Setup SSL / TLS
2. Install/Enable SSL / TLS
3. Enable SSL / TLS with a passphrase
4. Disable the RC4 ciphers
5. Find a command line utility that will enable you from your minion to connect to your master to verify the ciphers that you have disabled have actually been disabled 
6. Create a certificate in D.E.R format and try to make it work. Then convert the certificate back to PEM
7. Make it so the client browser trusts the certificate of the server 
8. Create a pkcs12 bundle for someone else and distribute it to them
